<div class="min-h-screen bg-[#f8f9fa]">
  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-r from-[#4361ee] to-[#3a0ca3] py-8 px-6">
    <!-- Hero Pattern Background -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20 bg-[url('data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width=\'60\' height=\'60\' viewBox=\'0 0 60 60\' xmlns=\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\'%3E%3Cg fill=\'none\' fill-rule=\'evenodd\'%3E%3Cg fill=\'%23ffffff\' fill-opacity=\'0.05\'%3E%3Cpath d=\'M36 34v-4h-2v4h-4v2h4v4h2v-4h4v-2h-4zm0-30V0h-2v4h-4v2h4v4h2V6h4V4h-4zM6 34v-4H4v4H0v2h4v4h2v-4h4v-2H6zM6 4V0H4v4H0v2h4v4h2V6h4V4H6z\'/%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/g%3E%3C/svg%3E')]">
    </div>
    <div class="container mx-auto relative z-10">
      <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-blue-100 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          How to Use MuDG
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-blue-100 mb-4 opacity-90">
          A powerful knowledge exploration tool that helps you navigate through complex topics,
          discover connections between ideas, and deepen your understanding through interactive conversation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-12 px-6">
    <div class="prose prose-stone prose-lg max-w-none mb-12">
      <h2>What is MuDG?</h2>
      <p>
        Dialectics is a method of reasoning that seeks to understand things in their movement and change. It is a way of thinking that is based on the idea that everything is interconnected and that change is constant. Dialectics is a powerful tool for understanding complex systems and for making sense of the world around us.
      </p>
      <p>
        As such MuDG (Multi-user Dialectic Graph) is a tool for thought. A multiplayer chat interface to allow the full reasoning behind an argument to be followed. Many people can think together to build out a massive knowledge graph, interacting with LLMs to integrate the knowledge into the whole.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-16">
      <%= for {instruction, index} <- @instructions |> Enum.with_index() do %>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-4 flex flex-col">
          <div class="h-48 w-full mb-4 bg-gray-50 rounded border border-gray-100 relative">
            <div
              id={"graph-" <> Integer.to_string(index)}
              class="w-full h-full info-graph absolute inset-0"
              data-graph={instruction.graph}
              data-node={instruction.node}
              data-cols={Jason.encode!(Dialectic.Consts.Colours.graph_cols())}
              data-updateview="false"
              data-div={"graph-" <> Integer.to_string(index)}
              phx-hook="Graph"
              phx-update="ignore"
            >
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 text-gray-900">{instruction.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600">{instruction.description}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
  
<!-- Why Dialectic? (Features) -->
